Privacy Policy
Effective Date: April 8, 2025

optizoom Studio develops and publishes apps and games that are offered as free and ad-supported. This Privacy Policy is intended to inform users about how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our applications.

Information Collection and Use
To improve our apps and deliver a better experience, we may collect certain information, including but not limited to device identifiers, usage data, and crash logs. This data is used solely for enhancing the functionality and performance of our apps.

We may also use third-party services that collect information used to identify you. These services may collect information such as your IP address, device type, operating system version, and usage patterns.

Third-party service providers we may use include:

Google Play Services: https://policies.google.com/privacy

AdMob: https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543?hl=en

Firebase Analytics: https://firebase.google.com/policies/analytics

Unity Ads: https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy

Facebook Audience Network: https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/

Log Data
When you use our apps and an error occurs, we may collect data and information (via third-party tools) called Log Data. This may include details such as your device's IP address, device name, operating system version, app settings at the time of the error, the time and date of use, and other statistics.

Cookies
Our services do not use cookies explicitly. However, the apps may use third-party libraries that use cookies to collect information and improve their services. You can manage cookie settings in your browser or device preferences.

Security
We value your trust in sharing your personal information with us. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it, please remember that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our apps are not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children. If we become aware that a child has provided us with personal data, we will take steps to delete it.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. You are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

Contact Us
